                  <font color="#FF0000" size="2"><b>Baron mode</b></font> <font size="2">is in other words - <b>Player Killing mode</b>.<br />
                  <br />
                  For you to be able to use Baron mode, you need family level 5, then right click another family with fam lvl 5 or above and select Force Attack(Baron mode). Once you click on force attack, you will be marked with a red skull above your family, and EVERYONE can attack you. If you die in Baron mode, you will lose an item from your inventory (you won&#39;t loose equiped items) and sometimes some exp points.<br />
                  <br />
                  When you kill someone you will get baron points, a baron level and a buff (decreses def, and increses atk), this buff increses with every baron level you gain.<br />
                  <br />
                  To lower your baron value (points), and get out of baron mode, you need to kill monsters of your level until the baron value goes back to 0.<br />
                  <br />
                  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />
                  <b>Baron City - Los Toldos</b><br />
                  <br />
                  Los toldos is the home city of the player killers, once you enter baron mode, if you go to the quarters or get killed, you will be sent to &quot;Los Toldos&quot;. Here you can get unique items, and some quests.<br />
                  <br />
                  If you talk to the npc (not the merchant) you can get the following costumes, if you have the necesary points and items.<br />
                  <br /></font>
                  <ul>
                    <li><font size="2">lvl 1 (1 baron points) no named tomb stone - The first one&#39;s free.</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">extra tomb stones, cost 5 soul crystals.</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">lvl 2 (2500 baron points)bloody coffin - 1 fanatic costume, 7 soul crystals</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">lvl 3 (5000 baron points) deadtly cross - 1 plate mail costume, 10 soul crystals</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">lvl 4 (10000 baron points) ghost - cross, 13 soul crystals</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">lvl 5 (20000 baron points) wheel of destiny - cross and ghost</font></li>
                  </ul><font size="2"><br />
                  Item Buffs:<br /></font>
                  <ol>
                    <li><font size="2">Tombstone- nothing</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">Bloody Coffin- DEF -5</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">Deadly Cross- DEF -10</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">Ghost- DEF -15, HP +800</font></li>
                    <li><font size="2">Wheel of Destiny- DEF -20, HP +800, AR +1, <span class="diffRemove">(DR+1?)</span><span class="diffAdd">DR-1</span></font></li>
                  </ol><br />
                  <div align="center">
                    _____________________<br />
                    <br />
                    <div align="left">
                      <font size="2">Other info about Los Toldos:<br /></font>
                      <ul>
                        <li><font size="2">Being Baron has its ups and downs; one of the things you can enjoy from Los Toldos, are the Baron Elite weapons and Baron UPCs.</font></li>
                      </ul><font size="2"><br /></font>
                      <ul>
                        <li><font size="2">Land of the Dead can only be accesed through Los Toldos (you need 1 mystery powder each time you want to enter)</font></li>
                      </ul><font size="2"><br />
                      Usefull Links:<br /></font>
